    {
      "id": 57,
      "type": "Note",
      "pos": [
        -96,
        -320
      ],
      "size": [
        608,
        320
      ],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 3,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "title": "Getting Started",
      "properties": {
        "text": "",
        "ue_properties": {
          "widget_ue_connectable": {},
          "version": "7.8",
          "input_ue_unconnectable": {}
        },
        "font_size": 18
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "HOW TO TRAIN A FOLEYTUNE LoRA\n\n1. Set your paths in the 3 purple string boxes below (Prompt, Input Folder, Output Folder)\n2. Run Step 1 (data pipeline) to filter, process, and extract features from your clips\n3. Copy the sweep.json path from Step 1's DatasetSaver output into the LoRA Scheduler\n4. Bypass Step 1 nodes, enable Step 2, and run training\n5. After training, enable Step 3 to test your adapter\n\nMinimum VRAM: 13 GB (bf16) or 8 GB (fp8)\nFull guide: LORA_TRAINING.md (in the custom node folder)\n\nhttps://github.com/ethanfel/ComfyUI-HunyuanVideo-FoleyTune/blob/main/LORA_TRAINING.md"
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    },
    {
      "id": 58,
      "type": "Note",
      "pos": [
        544,
        -320
      ],
      "size": [
        576,
        320
      ],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 4,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "title": "Step 1 Instructions",
      "properties": {
        "text": "",
        "ue_properties": {
          "widget_ue_connectable": {},
          "version": "7.8",
          "input_ue_unconnectable": {}
        },
        "font_size": 18
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "STEP 1 — DATA PIPELINE\n\n• Set 'Input Unfiltered Dataset Folder' to a folder of video files (.mp4, .mkv, etc)\n• Set 'Prompt' to describe the sound you're training (e.g. 'dog barking')\n• Set 'Output Filtered Dataset Folder' to where features will be saved\n• Adjust VideoQualityFilter's min_quality_score to control how strict filtering is\n• Run this step FIRST, then check the reports in the preview nodes on the right\n• Once happy with results, bypass all Step 1 nodes before running Step 2"
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    },
    {
      "id": 59,
      "type": "Note",
      "pos": [
        2048,
        -320
      ],
      "size": [
        608,
        320
      ],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 5,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "title": "Step 2 Instructions",
      "properties": {
        "text": "",
        "ue_properties": {
          "widget_ue_connectable": {},
          "version": "7.8",
          "input_ue_unconnectable": {}
        },
        "font_size": 18
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "STEP 2 — TRAINING\n\nOption A (recommended): Use the LoRA Scheduler node\n• Paste the sweep.json path from Step 1's DatasetSaver output\n• The sweep.json has all training settings — edit it to tune parameters\n• For 24GB GPUs: set gradient_checkpointing=true, batch_size=1, grad_accum=8\n\nOption B: Use the LoRA Trainer node directly (bypassed by default)\n• Set data_dir to your features folder from Step 1\n\nSee LORA_TRAINING.md for VRAM tips, sweep.json examples, and troubleshooting"
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    },
